For purposes of administration, review, and compliance monitoring, the Parties acknowledge the following timeline:
(a) 15 November 2025: Agreement executed;
(b) 20 November 2025: Security deposit due under Section 4.1;
(c) 1 December 2025: Delivery deadline under Section 6.1;
(d) 1 December 2025: Joint inspection and handover under Section 6.2;
(e) 5th day of each calendar month: Monthly rent due under Section 3.2;
(f) Upon occurrence of breach: Notice and cure process under Sections 5.3, 11.2;
(g) 30 days before Expiration Date: Renewal request deadline under Section 8.2;
(h) Upon expiration or early termination: Return, settlement, and post-termination obligations under Sections 9.1 to 9.3.
This timeline is for administrative reference only and does not alter the substantive obligations set out in the referenced sections.

7. Maintenance and Repair Allocation
During the Term:
(a) Party B shall use the Premises and all fixtures in a prudent and reasonable manner;
(b) Party B shall promptly notify Party A in writing of any damage, malfunction, leakage, electrical issue, or safety hazard;
(c) Party A shall repair structural defects and landlord-owned fixtures within five (5) days after receiving written notice, unless emergency conditions require immediate action, in which case Party A shall act within twenty-four (24) hours;
(d) if Party A fails to repair within such period, or if emergency conditions make prior notice impracticable, Party B may arrange necessary repairs and recover reasonable costs from Party A by written demand with supporting invoices, or offset such costs against rent only with Party A's prior written acknowledgment or a legally effective determination by a competent authority;
(e) if the repair materially interferes with Party B's use of the Premises for more than two (2) consecutive days, rent shall be reduced proportionately for the period of interference or the Term shall be extended by an equivalent period, as the Parties may agree in writing.
Damage caused by Party B's misuse, negligence, unauthorized alteration, or non-compliance with this Section 7 shall be repaired at Party B's sole cost and may trigger liability under Sections 4.3, 9.3, and 11.2(5).

10.2 Landlord's Right to Terminate
Party A may terminate this Agreement by written notice if Party B:
(1) fails to pay rent or other payable charges within thirty (30) days after written demand and expiry of the cure period under Section 11.2(2);
(2) unreasonably refuses to sign the handover record after the Premises satisfies the agreed delivery standard under Section 6.2, and such refusal is not cured within five (5) business days of written notice;
(3) alters the structure of the Premises without authorization in breach of Section 7 and fails to restore within ten (10) days of written notice;
(4) changes the permitted use in breach of Sections 1.2 and 8.1 and fails to cease such change within seven (7) days of written notice; or
(5) subleases or transfers possession in breach of Section 8.1.
In all cases, Party A shall exercise its termination right by written notice specifying the ground for termination and the effective date, which shall be no earlier than three (3) days after delivery of the notice. Party A shall not take self-help measures including locking access, removing personnel, or disposing of property without a legally effective court order or arbitral award, except in cases of genuine emergency posing immediate risk to life or property, in which case Party A shall notify Party B and the relevant authorities simultaneously and document the emergency circumstances.

11.1 Landlord Breach
If Party A is in breach:
(1) where Party B lawfully terminates under Section 10.3, Party A shall, within fifteen (15) days after the effective date of termination, return the Security Deposit and any unused prepaid rent, and pay liquidated damages equal to one (1) month's rent, without prejudice to additional losses proven by Party B;
(2) if Party A delays delivery or otherwise commits a breach under Section 10.3(2) or 10.3(3) but Party B does not terminate, Party A shall pay liquidated damages equal to two (2) times the daily rent for each day of breach, capped at two (2) months' rent in aggregate, and Party B may elect proportionate rent reduction or lease extension under Sections 6.1 and 8.2;
(3) if Party A purports to terminate this Agreement without a contractual basis under Section 10.2, Party A shall give at least thirty (30) days' written notice, return the Security Deposit and unused prepaid rent, and pay liquidated damages equal to two (2) months' rent, without prejudice to additional proven loss.
For the avoidance of doubt, cross-references in this Section to "Section 11.3" are references to Section 10.3 of this Agreement.

11.2 Tenant Breach
If Party B is in breach:
(1) where Party A lawfully terminates under Section 10.2, Party B shall pay liquidated damages equal to one (1) month's rent, without prejudice to additional losses proven by Party A;
(2) if Party B fails to pay rent, deposit, utilities, management fees, or other amounts due, Party A shall first issue written demand and grant a cure period of not less than five (5) days. If Party B still fails to pay and the breach does not yet trigger termination, or Party A elects not to terminate, Party B shall pay late damages equal to two (2) times the daily rent for each overdue day, calculated from the date the payment was due until the date of actual payment;
(3) if Party B purports to terminate this Agreement without a contractual basis under Section 10.3, Party B shall give at least thirty (30) days' written notice and pay liquidated damages equal to two (2) months' rent;
(4) if Party B fails to vacate or return the Premises on time under Section 9.1, Party B shall pay holdover damages at a rate of two (2) times the daily rent for each day of overdue vacation;
(5) if Party B performs unauthorized alteration, fit-out, installation, or other conduct prohibited by Section 7, Party B shall restore the Premises to its original condition within fifteen (15) days of written notice, compensate Party A for resulting loss supported by documented evidence, and indemnify Party A against third-party claims arising therefrom.
Before making any deduction from the Security Deposit or issuing a separate payment demand for losses, Party A shall provide Party B with a written itemized statement of claimed losses and supporting evidence within thirty (30) days of the event giving rise to the claim. Party B shall have ten (10) business days to respond. Undisputed amounts shall be paid or deducted within five (5) business days of the response period. Disputed amounts shall be resolved under Section 12.
